            <scopecontent id="aspace_9f4b52a1c5c0ce63a80e13faeeea93d0">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Schrieb-Kalender is printed in German. Entries are written primarily in German with some French and Latin.</p>
            </scopecontent>
            <c id="aspace_cdd566e35b8c4349b6e473826fd0feba" level="item">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Diary</unittitle>
                  <unitdatestructured unitdatetype="inclusive">
                     <datesingle standarddate="1801">1801</datesingle>
                  </unitdatestructured>
                  <container altrender="Paige 15"
                             id="aspace_bddd77ee6056c49e76e3ab09b158a253"
                             label="Mixed Materials"
                             localtype="Box">1</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_3c7dd85e4fc33cbe72832b01bfa88c4d">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Laid in at the front of the volume are:
- Two sheets denoting the translation of Joseph von Chlingensberg auf Berg's cipher
- A makeshift envelope, contemporary, that contains a letter from "Therese" (two bifolia and a single leaf) addressed to Joseph von Chlingensberg auf Berg.</p>
                  <p>Laid in throughout are notes (not contemporary).</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="aspace_38f534a59b77d3ac8c866380ce7c68d6" level="item">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Diary</unittitle>
